cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The method also involves incorporating spectral clustering into CNN, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The proposed method is evaluated on four public benchmarks, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, since the paper deals with security and privacy-related applications, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) could also be a possible sub-category.
